article.headline: Troy 66, Fla. International 59
article.story: TROY, Ala. (AP) -- O'Darien Bassett scored 26 points to help Troy break a five-game losing streak and defeat Florida International 66-59 on Saturday. Troy (11-16, 4-12 Sun Belt Conference) built a 12-point lead in the second half, but watched as Florida International's Alex Galindo hit a trio of 3-pointers down the stretch to tie the game at 59-59 with 2:21 left to play. Tom Jervis converted two free throws to give the Trojans the lead for good at 61-59, with just two minutes left. Bassett was 9-of-14 from the floor, 3-of-4 from behind the arc and 5-of-6 from the free throw line in the victory. Justin Jonus followed Bassett with 13 points, while Jervis added 10 points and four rebounds. Florida International (9-17, 6-10) was led by Galindo with 28 points.
